author: Luben Karavelov
message:
Don't pool buffers by default

Using soft/weak references could be harmful on some workloads.
We still provide the mechanism to use the `RecyclingBufferPool` but this
decision is now explicit.

message:
Remove pointer arithmetic

Looks like MSVC does not like it and returns C2036 error. Needed to
perform this change when integrating zstd into bazel to make it
compile under Windows:

https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/pull/11968/commits/02e0515d792efbd9d7cd168d1f23d246cd8b534a

author: Jeffrey Tolar
message:
Throw ZstdException instead of RuntimeException

The new ZstdException has methods to better programmatically inspect the
error.

Since ZstdException is a RuntimeException, this shouldn't cause any
API/ABI incompatibilities: things that caught the RuntimeException will
still catch the ZstdException, and things that ignored it will still be
able to do so.

Even though ZstdException is an unchecked exception, this commit
documents which methods may throw by adding `throws` clauses where
appropriate.

author: Davy Landman
message:
Stream ByteBuffer decompression

We start with the compressed file/stream as a (direct) ByteBuffer,
and can decompress from it with arbitrary sized buffers (even 1 byte
sizes buffers).

Especially useful with a memory mapped ByteBuffer, the OS can decide the
buffering etc.

author: Davy Landman
message:
Stream ByteBuffer decompression

We start with the compressed file/stream as a (direct) ByteBuffer,
and can decompress from it with arbitrary sized buffers (even 1 byte
sizes buffers).

Especially useful with a memory mapped ByteBuffer, the OS can decide the
buffering etc.

author: Adam Nelson
message:
Add Java wrappers and C implementations of compress/decompress using direct ByteBuffer

The wrappers work a bit differently than the ones that operate on byte[] due to the different semantics of ByteBuffer.  I've tried to make this implementation operate on the position(), capacity(), and limit() properties of the buffers in the idiomatic way.

message:
Handle another corner case

What the first frame has remainder =  ZSTD_DStreamInSize - 8

is making progress and read that byte if not.

author: luben karavelov
message:
Zstd streaming decompression done

Ignore the read size hints and read all the available
input up to ZSTD_DStreamInSize. This will handle when
when read hint = 1 that is ambigous (could mean read 1
byte or don't read, we have more data in the output
buffer.

This will also handle the skippable frames corner case
that was not handled correctly previously.

author: luben karavelov
message:
Finish the move to the new Zstd streaming API

On the decoding size we have gained ability to decode
multiple frames but we have lost:

- support for legacy formats bu it will be restored with
  zstd-1.0.0

- support for decoding un-finished streams, we have to
  figure out how it will play out with the multi-frame
  support.

Use the ZBUFF based streaming compression

It simplifies the whole interaction as the zstd is taking
care of the buffers, blocks and allignments so we don't have
to know anything about its internals.

author: Anders Daljord Morken
message:
Support OutputStream.write(int byte)

FilterOutputStream forwards write(int byte) directly to the underlying
stream, bypassing Zstd entirely.

Extend tests to exercise this for the first byte written in an existing
test case.

author: Anders Daljord Morken
message:
Add support for InputStream.read()

FilterInputStream forwards read() directly to the underlying stream,
bypassing Zstd entirely.

Extend tests to exercise this for the first byte read in a few test
cases.

author: luben karavelov
message:
Use direct byte biffers for the intermediate src/dst

It has better performance and does not hit a bug in JVM GCs
with pinned buffer in collectors different of G1GC

author: luben karavelov
message:
Fix the 32bit compatibility

We need to double cast the jlongs (always 64 bits)
through size_t (equals to pointer size) in order to
be able to cast it then as a pointer. Else we get
compiler warnings.

author: luben karavelov
message:
Fix the 32bit compatibility

We need to double cast the jlongs (always 64 bits)
through size_t (equals to pointer size) in order to
be able to cast it then as a pointer. Else we get
compiler warnings.
